00:00:06.373 --> 00:00:07.107 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gunshot]

00:00:07.140 --> 00:00:08.308 position:30% line:89% align:start
Eat this, pal!

00:00:08.342 --> 00:00:10.077 position:24% line:83% align:start
You're defenseless
under my counterattack.

00:00:10.778 --> 00:00:12.780 position:19% line:89% align:start
Yes, I was right! F.F.!

00:00:12.814 --> 00:00:14.114 position:35% line:83% align:start
Why is she
at the Discipline Cell?

00:00:17.785 --> 00:00:18.620 position:33% line:89% align:start
[F.F. gasps]

00:00:18.653 --> 00:00:19.419 position:30% line:89% align:start
[guard grunts]

00:00:20.454 --> 00:00:21.021 position:33% line:89% align:start
It's a disc.

00:00:23.123 --> 00:00:24.659 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[yells]
-Pale Snake is here somewhere!

00:00:24.692 --> 00:00:25.793 position:24% line:89% align:start
Shit! Where is he?

00:00:29.496 --> 00:00:30.497 position:30% line:89% align:start
[F.F.] No way!

00:00:30.532 --> 00:00:31.265 position:24% line:89% align:start
He's who threw it.

00:00:32.700 --> 00:00:34.636 position:35% line:89% align:start
Monster!

00:00:34.669 --> 00:00:36.671 position:16% line:83% align:start
Are you trying to tell me
that Pale Snake is really...

00:00:38.405 --> 00:00:38.806 position:35% line:89% align:start
I knew it!

00:00:40.173 --> 00:00:41.174 position:19% line:89% align:start
You are Father Pucchi.

00:00:43.343 --> 00:00:45.145 position:30% line:83% align:start
["STONE OCEAN"
by ichigo playing]

00:02:14.068 --> 00:02:15.369 position:35% line:83% align:start
[narrator]
The thing F.F. feared most

00:02:15.402 --> 00:02:17.137 position:10% line:89% align:start
was not their body vanishing.

00:02:17.170 --> 00:02:19.540 position:19% line:83% align:start
Rather, what they found
most frightening of all

00:02:19.574 --> 00:02:21.509 position:19% line:83% align:start
was potentially losing
their intellect

00:02:21.542 --> 00:02:22.877 position:24% line:83% align:start
and being unable to
get it back.

00:02:25.046 --> 00:02:27.015 position:10% line:89% align:start
[F.F.] I remember everything

00:02:27.048 --> 00:02:29.383 position:13% line:83% align:start
since the day I met Jolyne
on the farm.

00:02:29.416 --> 00:02:32.185 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's still so clear, it might
as well have been yesterday.

00:02:32.219 --> 00:02:34.956 position:24% line:83% align:start
The weird scribbles
on the public phones.

00:02:34.989 --> 00:02:36.891 position:19% line:83% align:start
The fluffed-up blankets
on the bed,

00:02:36.924 --> 00:02:38.926 position:19% line:89% align:start
the stink of the trash.

00:02:38.960 --> 00:02:40.695 position:21% line:83% align:start
The guards screaming
and yelling.

00:02:40.728 --> 00:02:43.064 position:19% line:83% align:start
The sound of the doors
opening and closing.

00:02:43.097 --> 00:02:45.566 position:13% line:83% align:start
Hearing the toilet flushing
all day long.

00:02:45.600 --> 00:02:47.334 position:24% line:83% align:start
I even remember all
those silly talks

00:02:47.367 --> 00:02:49.169 position:7% line:89% align:start
with Jolyne and everyone else,

00:02:49.202 --> 00:02:51.371 position:19% line:89% align:start
laughing hysterically.

00:02:51.405 --> 00:02:55.076 position:10% line:83% align:start
But still, even though I live
at the farm for many years,

00:02:55.109 --> 00:02:57.845 position:27% line:83% align:start
I don't remember
anything from before that.

00:02:57.879 --> 00:03:00.447 position:10% line:83% align:start
All I can pull from that time
are robotic thoughts,

00:03:00.480 --> 00:03:02.850 position:19% line:89% align:start
almost like recordings.

00:03:02.884 --> 00:03:04.886 position:16% line:89% align:start
I simply followed orders.

00:03:04.919 --> 00:03:07.555 position:30% line:83% align:start
And my task was
to protect Pale Snake's discs

00:03:07.588 --> 00:03:09.657 position:30% line:83% align:start
without knowing
or even asking why.

00:03:09.691 --> 00:03:11.559 position:16% line:89% align:start
I finally understand now

00:03:11.592 --> 00:03:14.762 position:24% line:83% align:start
that living is more
than just being alive.

00:03:14.796 --> 00:03:17.065 position:16% line:89% align:start
It means making memories.

00:03:17.098 --> 00:03:19.332 position:30% line:83% align:start
If I lose that,
I'll lose everything.

00:03:20.902 --> 00:03:24.005 position:7% line:83% align:start
Jolyne takes all these actions
on behalf of her dad,

00:03:24.038 --> 00:03:26.007 position:21% line:83% align:start
and risks her life to
help Ermes

00:03:26.040 --> 00:03:28.275 position:16% line:83% align:start
and the few other people
she trusts.

00:03:28.308 --> 00:03:32.180 position:16% line:83% align:start
Because she has pleasant
memories from living her life.

00:03:32.212 --> 00:03:34.649 position:13% line:83% align:start
That's the remarkable thing
about humans.

00:03:34.682 --> 00:03:35.516 position:30% line:89% align:start
Their memories

00:03:36.416 --> 00:03:38.485 position:13% line:89% align:start
gives their cells courage.

00:03:38.519 --> 00:03:42.156 position:10% line:89% align:start
The knowledge that I am F.F.,

00:03:42.190 --> 00:03:43.624 position:24% line:83% align:start
I've never had that
in the past.

00:03:45.560 --> 00:03:45.960 position:35% line:89% align:start
That's it.

00:03:47.095 --> 00:03:47.695 position:35% line:89% align:start
I know it.

00:03:48.696 --> 00:03:52.365 position:30% line:83% align:start
That... That is
what intellect is.

00:03:55.335 --> 00:03:58.405 position:19% line:83% align:start
What's it going to be?
Am I your utmost priority?

00:03:58.438 --> 00:04:02.143 position:19% line:83% align:start
Or is it more important
to snuff out D an' G's life

00:04:02.176 --> 00:04:03.978 position:13% line:83% align:start
-to try and save Jolyne's?
-[D an' G grunts]

00:04:04.011 --> 00:04:04.812 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:04:07.715 --> 00:04:08.616 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:04:08.649 --> 00:04:10.651 position:10% line:89% align:start
You hesitated. It's too late!

00:04:10.685 --> 00:04:11.986 position:35% line:83% align:start
That moment
will cost your life.

00:04:15.056 --> 00:04:15.990 position:41% line:89% align:start
[yells]

00:04:17.992 --> 00:04:18.793 position:33% line:89% align:start
[F.F. groans]

00:04:19.527 --> 00:04:20.862 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chokes]

00:04:20.895 --> 00:04:23.965 position:10% line:83% align:start
Do you even know why you have
your intellect and powers?

00:04:23.998 --> 00:04:25.499 position:13% line:89% align:start
Because I gave them to you.

00:04:26.567 --> 00:04:28.035 position:10% line:89% align:start
And now I'm taking them back.

00:04:29.804 --> 00:04:31.806 position:10% line:83% align:start
[F.F.] When I need to kick up
my courage,

00:04:31.839 --> 00:04:34.976 position:21% line:89% align:start
I think about Jolyne.

00:04:35.009 --> 00:04:37.912 position:7% line:89% align:start
Those very things are memories.

00:04:37.945 --> 00:04:41.149 position:7% line:89% align:start
And this... this is intellect.

00:04:41.182 --> 00:04:42.517 position:19% line:83% align:start
-[Father Pucchi gasps]
-[D an' G yells]

00:04:43.316 --> 00:04:44.051 position:21% line:89% align:start
What? What the hell?

00:04:46.020 --> 00:04:47.755 position:27% line:89% align:start
[grunts, groans]

00:04:52.093 --> 00:04:52.927 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Father Pucchi]
It couldn't be...

00:04:54.061 --> 00:04:55.696 position:7% line:89% align:start
What on Earth did F.F. just do?

00:04:56.329 --> 00:04:57.632 position:38% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:04:57.665 --> 00:04:58.365 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:04:58.398 --> 00:04:59.499 position:5% line:89% align:start
[D an' G] Pale...[Father Pucchi]

00:04:59.534 --> 00:05:01.368 position:30% line:83% align:start
She infused him
with her own body fluids.

00:05:07.542 --> 00:05:09.309 position:19% line:89% align:start
No! I can't believe it!

00:05:09.342 --> 00:05:10.745 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:05:13.380 --> 00:05:13.881 position:27% line:89% align:start
[YA-YA MA snorts]

00:05:15.716 --> 00:05:16.884 position:38% line:89% align:start
I am a...

00:05:22.557 --> 00:05:26.027 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Anastasia] Well, well,
it seems F.F. pulled it off.

00:05:26.060 --> 00:05:27.895 position:21% line:83% align:start
They killed the User
like they said they would.

00:05:30.231 --> 00:05:31.132 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:05:31.165 --> 00:05:32.867 position:7% line:89% align:start
There's nothing inside the pod!

00:05:32.900 --> 00:05:33.466 position:24% line:89% align:start
[breathes heavily]

00:05:35.570 --> 00:05:37.071 position:13% line:89% align:start
[suspenseful music playing]

00:05:42.910 --> 00:05:43.578 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[gasps]
-[wings flapping]

00:05:47.114 --> 00:05:47.615 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:05:49.250 --> 00:05:50.084 position:19% line:89% align:start
What the hell is that?

00:05:51.919 --> 00:05:53.420 position:30% line:83% align:start
Does this mean
that thing was born?

00:05:54.755 --> 00:05:56.924 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Jolyne] Is this
what Pale Snake's

00:05:56.958 --> 00:05:57.625 position:13% line:89% align:start
been after the whole time?

00:06:01.428 --> 00:06:03.598 position:19% line:89% align:start
Oh, my god! What is it?

00:06:04.932 --> 00:06:07.367 position:33% line:83% align:start
What purpose
was it conceived to serve?

00:06:07.400 --> 00:06:09.103 position:21% line:83% align:start
And why does it need
to be here specifically?

00:06:10.470 --> 00:06:12.273 position:16% line:83% align:start
Were the prisoners turned
into plants

00:06:12.306 --> 00:06:14.976 position:24% line:83% align:start
just so this thing
can finally be born?

00:06:15.009 --> 00:06:16.476 position:13% line:89% align:start
And what's even weirder is

00:06:16.510 --> 00:06:19.280 position:19% line:83% align:start
I stop becoming a plant
because it was born.

00:06:19.313 --> 00:06:20.681 position:35% line:83% align:start
But I guess
it doesn't matter anymore.

00:06:23.951 --> 00:06:24.451 position:35% line:89% align:start
[both gasp]

00:06:30.324 --> 00:06:32.459 position:30% line:83% align:start
Don't you dare
let F.F. get away from you!

00:06:32.492 --> 00:06:35.329 position:24% line:83% align:start
Retrieve her disc,
and read every memory on it.

00:06:35.363 --> 00:06:36.964 position:19% line:83% align:start
Locate the whereabouts
of that thing

00:06:36.998 --> 00:06:40.735 position:21% line:83% align:start
born from Dio's bone
and then go track it down.

00:06:40.768 --> 00:06:42.435 position:13% line:89% align:start
[F.F.] I'm totally exposed,

00:06:42.469 --> 00:06:44.939 position:24% line:83% align:start
I may not even last
30 seconds out there.

00:06:44.972 --> 00:06:48.943 position:10% line:83% align:start
I need water. I have to find
a way to get back to Jolyne

00:06:48.976 --> 00:06:50.912 position:33% line:83% align:start
and tell her
who Pale Snake really is.

00:06:50.945 --> 00:06:51.145 position:27% line:89% align:start
[engine rumbling]

00:06:52.046 --> 00:06:52.546 position:41% line:89% align:start
Dammit!

00:06:53.547 --> 00:06:54.682 position:27% line:89% align:start
She needs to know

00:06:54.715 --> 00:06:56.517 position:24% line:83% align:start
it's Father Pucchi,
the freaking chaplain!

00:06:57.952 --> 00:06:58.653 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:06:59.720 --> 00:07:00.788 position:10% line:89% align:start
Let me guess!You're thirsty a

00:07:00.821 --> 00:07:03.423 position:30% line:83% align:start
nd trying to go
to the tap out front.

00:07:03.456 --> 00:07:04.992 position:44% line:83% align:start
Well,
before you hurry off, dear,

00:07:05.026 --> 00:07:07.828 position:19% line:83% align:start
wait as I have quite an
important question to ask you.

00:07:07.862 --> 00:07:08.162 position:33% line:89% align:start
[F.F. grunts]

00:07:11.332 --> 00:07:13.134 position:27% line:83% align:start
Sorry, gotta go!
But here's my answer!

00:07:14.168 --> 00:07:14.702 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:07:17.338 --> 00:07:17.838 position:35% line:89% align:start
[shatters]

00:07:18.673 --> 00:07:20.007 position:19% line:89% align:start
[F.F. screams in pain]

00:07:23.778 --> 00:07:24.912 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gunshot]

00:07:24.946 --> 00:07:26.180 position:21% line:89% align:start
[F.F. yells, grunts]

00:07:28.382 --> 00:07:29.817 position:41% line:89% align:start
[yells]

00:07:29.850 --> 00:07:31.018 position:35% line:89% align:start
[whimpers]

00:07:31.052 --> 00:07:34.088 position:16% line:83% align:start
Now, about that question
I wanted to ask you, F.F.

00:07:34.121 --> 00:07:36.023 position:7% line:89% align:start
Well, are you listening to me?

00:07:36.891 --> 00:07:39.260 position:7% line:89% align:start
Tell me the truth, I'm curious.

00:07:39.293 --> 00:07:41.162 position:30% line:83% align:start
Did you happen
to get a good look

00:07:41.195 --> 00:07:43.496 position:10% line:83% align:start
at the miracle that was just
born in the Discipline Cells?

00:07:44.432 --> 00:07:46.400 position:10% line:89% align:start
What kind of organism was it?

00:07:46.434 --> 00:07:48.302 position:19% line:89% align:start
Was it animal or plant?

00:07:48.336 --> 00:07:50.004 position:21% line:89% align:start
And was it beautiful?

00:07:50.037 --> 00:07:51.038 position:19% line:89% align:start
You tell me something.

00:07:51.072 --> 00:07:52.974 position:16% line:83% align:start
What's a priest like you
doing at this prison?

00:07:53.007 --> 00:07:54.809 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'm sure it isn't
for anything noble.

00:07:54.842 --> 00:07:58.245 position:7% line:83% align:start
Hush! I'm the one who's asking
the questions. Thank you!

00:07:58.279 --> 00:08:00.815 position:16% line:83% align:start
You see! If I simply take
your memories and read them,

00:08:00.848 --> 00:08:03.351 position:19% line:83% align:start
I would know the nature
of what was born immediately.

00:08:03.384 --> 00:08:04.719 position:33% line:89% align:start
[F.F. gasps]

00:08:04.752 --> 00:08:06.520 position:10% line:89% align:start
However, I would much rather

00:08:06.554 --> 00:08:08.456 position:13% line:83% align:start
hear your personal account
of it.

00:08:08.488 --> 00:08:10.558 position:21% line:83% align:start
Because saying thing
such as "it was soft,"

00:08:10.591 --> 00:08:12.893 position:10% line:83% align:start
or "it was a strange color,"
or "it was lovely,"

00:08:12.927 --> 00:08:14.729 position:38% line:83% align:start
are your
self-generated thoughts,

00:08:14.762 --> 00:08:17.765 position:10% line:83% align:start
and not the memories actually
embedded within your disc.

00:08:17.798 --> 00:08:19.367 position:38% line:83% align:start
I get it.
You're worried that thing

00:08:19.400 --> 00:08:21.402 position:27% line:83% align:start
is gonna run away
and disappear, huh?

00:08:21.435 --> 00:08:22.903 position:7% line:89% align:start
And you would lose it forever.

00:08:22.937 --> 00:08:25.973 position:16% line:83% align:start
Huh? What are you saying?
It's already moved?

00:08:26.007 --> 00:08:27.575 position:16% line:89% align:start
[F.F.] Maybe! Who knows?

00:08:27.608 --> 00:08:28.943 position:13% line:89% align:start
To be honest, you should be

00:08:28.976 --> 00:08:31.746 position:16% line:83% align:start
way more worried about it
being killed, much less moved.

00:08:31.779 --> 00:08:35.082 position:13% line:83% align:start
Actually, I take that back,
it might be dead already.

00:08:35.116 --> 00:08:38.219 position:21% line:83% align:start
I mean the guy Jolyne
is with is kind of a dick.

00:08:38.252 --> 00:08:40.921 position:24% line:83% align:start
I know he'd kill it
if he thought it was dangerous.

00:08:40.955 --> 00:08:42.590 position:33% line:83% align:start
Killing it is
not only difficult,

00:08:42.623 --> 00:08:44.959 position:19% line:83% align:start
it's quite impossible.
There is no way!

00:08:46.327 --> 00:08:47.928 position:21% line:83% align:start
It possesses far too
much power

00:08:47.962 --> 00:08:49.397 position:16% line:83% align:start
and strength to fall prey
to that.

00:08:49.430 --> 00:08:50.965 position:21% line:89% align:start
It's indestructible.

00:08:50.998 --> 00:08:53.502 position:24% line:83% align:start
My concern is that
Jolyne will get sidetracked

00:08:53.534 --> 00:08:55.736 position:21% line:83% align:start
to do something rash
and lose sight of it.

00:08:55.770 --> 00:08:58.572 position:13% line:83% align:start
Only Jotaro's memories can
control what has been born.

00:08:58.606 --> 00:09:00.107 position:21% line:89% align:start
That is what matters.

00:09:00.141 --> 00:09:03.411 position:16% line:83% align:start
And I have those memories
in my clutches now.

00:09:03.444 --> 00:09:05.079 position:21% line:83% align:start
We have finally come
to the point

00:09:05.112 --> 00:09:06.247 position:13% line:89% align:start
where we're one step away.

00:09:06.280 --> 00:09:07.815 position:7% line:89% align:start
What was his bodily form like?

00:09:07.848 --> 00:09:09.350 position:19% line:89% align:start
Did it develop quickly?

00:09:09.383 --> 00:09:11.118 position:21% line:83% align:start
Did it show response
to stimuli?

00:09:12.620 --> 00:09:15.589 position:7% line:83% align:start
I thought if it hit the water,
it would drown.

00:09:15.623 --> 00:09:18.759 position:30% line:83% align:start
Uh, what else?
Yeah, I don't quite remember.

00:09:18.793 --> 00:09:20.194 position:13% line:89% align:start
Ugh, okay, well... It's...

00:09:21.695 --> 00:09:23.631 position:16% line:83% align:start
She's stalling for time!
Quick! Behind you!

00:09:24.865 --> 00:09:25.599 position:44% line:89% align:start
Ugh!

00:09:26.600 --> 00:09:28.436 position:21% line:89% align:start
[F.F.] Hah, I did it!

00:09:28.469 --> 00:09:30.471 position:30% line:83% align:start
Oh, by the way,
F.F.'s intellect,

00:09:30.505 --> 00:09:32.973 position:13% line:83% align:start
its control tower's nowhere
near here.

00:09:33.007 --> 00:09:34.642 position:30% line:89% align:start
It's that way!

00:09:34.675 --> 00:09:37.111 position:33% line:83% align:start
Even better,
I've got water now!

00:09:37.144 --> 00:09:39.313 position:21% line:83% align:start
Which means I can go
and tell Jolyne all of it.

00:09:46.187 --> 00:09:47.288 position:35% line:89% align:start
[trilling]

00:09:49.090 --> 00:09:50.291 position:24% line:89% align:start
Intellect, you say?

00:09:50.324 --> 00:09:53.394 position:7% line:83% align:start
You're not the one who decides
where your intellect is.

00:09:53.427 --> 00:09:55.596 position:24% line:83% align:start
These powers belong
to someone else.

00:09:55.629 --> 00:09:57.465 position:21% line:83% align:start
In fact, it's the one
who graciously

00:09:57.498 --> 00:09:59.300 position:38% line:83% align:start
gave you
your Stand power with a disc.

00:09:59.333 --> 00:09:59.667 position:47% line:89% align:start
Me!

00:10:01.836 --> 00:10:03.671 position:24% line:83% align:start
You sentient bag of
plankton! You're e

00:10:03.704 --> 00:10:04.939 position:13% line:77% align:start
xplaining things to me You
sentient bag of plankton! You're
explaining things to me

00:10:04.972 --> 00:10:06.207 position:21% line:83% align:start
with unearned triumph
and arrogance?

00:10:06.240 --> 00:10:07.341 position:33% line:89% align:start
How dare you!

00:10:07.374 --> 00:10:08.008 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

